items.title: DYSTODCAST - 002 - FANTASM - "Ecos Profundos: El Regreso de las Resonancias"
items.description:
Fantasm, el nombre artístico de Kenzo Meservey, es una estrella en ascenso en la escena del techno industrial y el rave. Nacido en Los Ángeles, descubrió su amor por el techno a una edad temprana y comenzó a producir música hace solo un año. Fantasm, que ahora reside en Lyon, Francia, crea música inspirada en su entorno, conocido por sus potentes kicks y su atmósfera oscura, lo que le ha valido seguidores leales en la comunidad techno.

A pesar de su corto tiempo en la industria, los sets de DJ enérgicos y dinámicos de Fantasm ya lo han convertido en un talento reconocido. Tiene objetivos ambiciosos para su carrera, apuntando a romper la pista de baile y llevar la energía de la multitud a nuevas alturas, al igual que 999999999. Aspira a ser tan hábil técnicamente como Nico Moreno, evocar emociones intensas como Trym e igualar las actuaciones electrizantes de I Hate Models. Con su dedicación a su oficio y su sonido único, Fantasm continuará superando los límites del techno y dejando una huella indeleble en la industria.

@FANTASM

items.description:
Common Poetry is the most recognized Hard Industrial techno DJ duo in Latin America and are founders of Rubber Mind: record label and party organiser. Based in Bogotá, Colombia. Their sets are characterized by combining heavy hitting kicks and progressions between hard techno, rawstyle, reverse bass with industrial aesthetics, dark, energetic and euphoric atmospheres. 

The artists had toured around the world including Europe, Asia, North, Central and South America since 2020. Currently they are the fresh face of the Colombian industrial techno scene with their unique, energetic performances and high technical mixing skills. 
Their new vinyl release DANCE ELIXIR represents their raw sound and Colombian vision of hard techno, soon they will release new singles and an EP.

items.title: 2006-09 Magda - She's A Dancing Machine (Full Mix)
items.description:
MAGDA 
She’s a Dancing Machine

Evolution is a fuzzy thing when it comes to electronic dance music, especially when left in the hands of certain DJ’s. From experimental to disco to pop to house and everything in between and to come, the mutation is the now and new. Known for mutations of her own, MAGDA, the Berlin resident DJ and producer, brings her influences and creations full circle in this runway soundtrack act SHE’S A DANCING MACHINE. Through over thirty tracks of classic and fresh as hell dance burners, the selection and style is reflective yet reactive to what “minimal” music and mix albums ought to create. From robotic hustles to disco house sprinkler moves and electro-tech windmills, Magda turns the years back to phuture.

Equal parts perspiration and inspiration, SHE’S A DANCING MACHINE delivers with micro-edits, custom loops and lofty effects, born out of her DJ ascension from beating the bits out of her Final Scratch in clubs. The mix has the range you’d expect with top shelf artists included such as Metro Area, Ricardo Villalobos, Marc Houle and Robert Babicz and sets up some surprises from decades past by dropping in Larry Heard and Portion Control. Amongst personal favorites from The Persuader (Svek’s Jesper Dahlbäck) she’s not afraid to loop in her own productions from Minus and her new label (along with Marc Houle and Troy Pierce), Items & Things.

SHE’S A DANCING MACHINE paints the experience and attitude from a night with Magda in control at the decks. Since the turn of the millennium she’s been building a steady fan base throughout Europe, North America and Japan with a few residencies built by demand, charming us along the way with a smile. Magda has taken the chosen not given path of a DJ with a mission- searching, finding and carving her own path from being a slave to the rhythm.

items.title: Suburban Mix 210 - X tin
items.description:
Suburban Mix 210 - X tin (@x_ti_n)

Get ready to immerse yourself in X tin's electrifying energy as she commands the spotlight in the 210th episode of Suburban Mix.

Austrian-born, X tin uses sound to connect to the crowd through deep emotions and fills up the room with atmospheric intense trips in waveform. Berlin as her recent hometown by choice, shaped her, exploring worlds between dark dystopian techno, hypnotic and experimental ambient, which she blends in non genre specific mixes since 2015. Distorted ambiences, blurring lines between styles and layering sceneries, while never lacking a specific taste and powerful character. An eclectic choice of rhythms are sending travelers through deep ambient, mesmerizing electronic up to dark hypnotic- and energetic industrial techno. 
Her signature is described by a room full of intense feelings, sweat and a never lost lust for moving bodies.

items.title: New Brvtalism No. 289 - Aurora
items.description:
The Brvtalist is proud to present a new mix from Aurora. The DJ and producer from Belgrade, Serbia has been one of the city's most important artists, releasing music on labels like Organism, Subsist Records, Induxtriall Records, Substantiv and more. She has continuously been active around Europe and beyond and for New Brvtalism No. 289 she showcases her diverse taste with this electrifying mix.
